[SN]TITLE[SN]
A18 crash: Man killed in Isle of Man van smash named

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 22-year-old van driver killed in a collision with another van in the Isle of Man has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Ben Collister, of Ballasalla died in the crash on the A18 Mountain Road, near the Mountain Box, on Friday.
Police said Mr Collister was driving towards Ramsey in a white Citroen Berlingo, while a blue Ford Transit was travelling the other way.
The Transit driver was taken to hospital but his injuries were not thought to be life-threatening.
